{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 08:30:59.877666", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary assessment\\n- Overall network health: Normal. Control-plane (OSPF) adjacencies are up and stable across core, distribution, and the server access router. Data-plane connectivity between user subnets (10.1.1.0/24, 10.2.1.0/24) and the server farm (10.200.0.0/24) is working with 0% packet loss and low latency. DNS resolution for the local zone functions correctly. The HTTP load balancer (web99.local) returns 200 OK with consistent TTFB and total times.\\n- Security/policy check: The backend servers on 20.200.0.0/24 are not reachable from host networks, as intended. Only the load balancer has access to those backends.\\n\\nKey observations and evidence\\n\\n1) Control plane (OSPF)\\n- Core and distribution routing tables include expected subnets:\\n  - router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1 receive 10.200.0.0/24 and the opposite host subnet via the core. Each has its directly connected user subnet as expected.\\n  - router_core_1/core_2/core_3 route 10.200.0.0/24 via the server access side, and 10.1.1.0/24 and 10.2.1.0/24 via the appropriate cores/distribution.\\n  - server_access_router learns 10.1.1.0/24 and 10.2.1.0/24 via its core-facing link (172.16.0.10/31), and has 10.200.0.0/24 directly connected on br0.\\n- OSPF adjacencies:\\n  - router_core_1: Full with its core neighbors (show ip ospf neighbor shows three Full/DR adjacencies).\\n  - server_access_router: OSPF neighbor is Full with core_3 (Full/Backup on eth7). The adjacency is stable.\\n\\n2) Data plane reachability\\n- End-to-end ICMP tests (functions.get_reachability) show 0% loss between servers, load balancer, and hosts:\\n  - dns_server -> host_2_1_1_1 OK\\n  - dhcp_server -> host_2_1_1_1 OK\\n  - hosts -> load_balancer OK\\n  - web_server_[0–3] -> host_2_1_1_1 OK\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> dns_server OK (rtt ~3.6 ms avg)\\n- HTTP service checks:\\n  - From host_1_1_1_1 to web99.local: TTFB ~0.27–0.33 s, total ~1.07–1.13 s across runs; all successful.\\n  - From host_2_1_1_1 to web99.local: TTFB ~0.23–0.42 s, total ~1.02–1.22 s; all successful.\\n  - From host_1_1_1_1 to web0.local…web3.local: all return 200 with similar latency characteristics.\\n- Load balancer internals:\\n  - nginx is listening on 0.0.0.0:80 and active (running).\\n  - nginx upstream config points to 20.200.0.2, .3, .4.\\n  - From load_balancer to backends (20.200.0.2–.4): ICMP success; HTTP returns code 200 with TTFB ~0.26–0.39 s and total ~1.07–1.20 s.\\n- DNS:\\n  - Name resolution on host resolves web0.local–web3.local to 10.200.0.3–.6 and web99.local to 10.200.0.7 as expected.\\n  - ICMP to DNS server (10.200.0.2) from host_1_1_1_1 is successful.\\n\\n3) Policy/isolation of backend servers\\n- Hosts cannot reach 20.200.0.0/24:\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 ping to 20.200.0.1 returns “Destination Net Unreachable” from 10.1.1.1 (distribution router), confirming no route is advertised for 20.200.0.0/24 into the enterprise. Ping to 20.200.0.2 fails (timeout). This matches the design goal that backend web servers are not directly accessible from hosts.\\n\\n4) Minor observations\\n- OSPF interface type on server_access_router eth7 shows a DR/BDR election on a /31 link (Full/Backup). While not impacting current operation, it indicates the interface is using a broadcast-type OSPF network on what appears to be a point-to-point /31. Adjacency is stable and routing is correct.\\n- Occasional small variability in name lookup/connect times in curl tests (e.g., sporadic ~80–90 ms namelookup spikes) was observed but did not affect successful page delivery and overall times remained low.\\n\\nConclusions\\n\\n- Anomaly detection: No functional anomalies detected. Control plane adjacencies are established and stable; routing tables are correct; data plane connectivity and HTTP services are operating normally; DNS is resolving correctly.\\n- Fault localization: No faulty devices identified. All tested routers, servers, and the load balancer behave as expected.\\n- Root cause (if any): Not applicable; no service-impacting fault found.\\n\\nThe network currently meets its design objectives, including correct OSPF reachability for user and server networks, successful access to web services via web servers and the load balancer, correct DNS behavior, and enforced isolation of backend servers (20.200.0.0/24) from host networks., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='0f904b2e-10c0-4554-b284-e666762779ab'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
